<script type="text/javascript">
function togPhase(n) {
	var e = document.getElementById('phasehint' + n);
	e.style.display = e.style.display == 'none' ? 'block' : 'none';
}
function togAllPhases(display) {
	for (var i = 1; i <= 50; i++) {
		var e = document.getElementById('phasehint' + i);
		if (!e) break;
		e.style.display = display;
	}
}
function addHint(n) {
	var e = document.getElementById('phase');
	for (var i = 0; i < e.childNodes.length; i++) {
		e.childNodes[i].selected = e.childNodes[i].value == n ? 'selected' : '';
	}
	e = document.getElementById('text');
	e.focus();
	e.select();
}
</script>

<div class="mm white">
This quest <span class="blue">[<span class="yellow">1019</span>]</span> is called '<span class="yellow">Back in Black</span>',<br/>
for Adventurers levels <span class="yellow">181</span> to <span class="yellow">241</span>.<br />


<span class="hg"><a href="/npc/647">Lord Agrippa</a> [<a href="/area/48">Runic Castle</a>] is the master in charge of this quest.</span><br />

My mages have devised another plan to stop the demons in Avarice.  They<br />
wish to augment a Momentary Darkness spell to such an effect that it will<br />
permanently shield Avarice from the outside world and thus end the dangers<br />
posed by these hideously evil creatures in Dungeon Avarice.  Brave<br />
adventurer, your help is needed in recovering these items of power for my<br />
mages to use in their work.  Do hurry back as time is of the essence, if the<br />
spells are not set in time the opportunity for using this method will not<br />
come again for five decades.  For your efforts you will be well-rewarded<br />
indeed, just take care lest you too are lost to us.  May the Powers go with<br />
you as you seek to help us end this threat to Alyria!<br />

<span class="hy">Upon successful completion of this quest you can receive:</span><br />

<span class="hm">*</span>Up to <span class="yellow">80</span> quest points, <span class="yellow">9</span> practice points, <span class="yellow">38,000</span> experience points,<br/>
&nbsp;<span class="yellow">0</span> build points, <span class="yellow">0</span> piety, and <span class="yellow">17,000</span> gold pieces.<br />


You have <span class="yellow">350</span> minutes remaining to complete this quest.<br />

Back in Black consists of:<br />


